es with Gerber's potential, and which\nagrees with the author's previous works.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Oct 2005 12:03:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Dec 2005 18:08:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2006 10:06:28 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 20 Jan 2006 16:16:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-10-06"}
